6:
How could you, Al?! Do you have any
idea how worried we were?!
10:
Yes, ma'am. Sorry, ma'am. It was
very wrong of me to do that.
26:
We're telling this little knucklehead
off! Al, did you think you would look
cool if you just rushed in there by
yourself?!
31:
Alk, I do not want you to be
influenced by Light in this way.
38:
Who is this... Voo-Voo of which you
speak?
41:
Huh? Well, duh, It's you, of course!
Your name's Malviola, so I shortened
it to Voo-Voo!
46:
And WHY did my name warrant
shortening?!
50:
You don't like it? Hmm... What about
Mallie then?
54:
Wait, we can talk about this later! I'm
in the middle of a lecture! You
remember how badly hurt Alk was,
right?!
57:
Ah... Now that you mention it, there
were grave injuries on his shoulder,
chest, and stomach...
62: Wait... How did you know that?
66:
...I couldn't very well put him to bed
in wet clothes, could I?
71:
Oh. My. GOSH! Wait, are you
serious?! Oh, the girls have GOT to
hear about this!
77:
Can't you leave me out of your
gossip?!
81:
Ugh, do as you wish. I couldn't care
less.
83:
Alk. Stella. I am headed to the
Kaleidoscope. Could I ask you to
accompany me?
87: Hm? What for? Can I come?
99:
I apologize for my lack of concern,
but perhaps you should play friends
with someone else.
104:
I'm not falling for that cold and
reserved act! We're already friends!
109:
Now then, let us begin.
Activate acceleration!
113:
Whoa... This device tracks data on
the changes in the world, right?
116:
I believe you call them "shifts" here,
correct? This is exactly the reaction I
was expecting.
118:
The elements here are unstable. It's
like they don't know what to do with
themselves...
122:
This truly is the perfect place for my
research.
124:
But I'm sure I don't need to tell YOU
that, do I?
131:
I understand your irritation. The
ruckus of the surface makes it so
difficult to pursue the truth, doesn't it?
133:
But I can't say I enjoy being spied
upon either.
142:
You and I are one and the same.
Both of us seek to understand the
darkness.
145:
But neither one of us has the power
to achieve that goal on our own.
Which is why I suggest we work
together.
150:
How dare you... If you truly seek the
darkness, little girl...
153: Then be consumed by my shadows!
165: Hmph, what a nasty man you are...
168:
We've reached our limits! Sir, we
need to stop the experiment now!
170:
I-it won't stop! We can't stop it!
We're doomed!
171:
At this rate, our world... Our very
reality
173:
Malviola... Have you... always had
that power?
179:
As you can see, my colleagues
feared my power and blamed the
experiment's failure on me.
182:
No one tried to correct them. No one
bothered to help me.
185:
But what of it? Are you trying to
discourage me from trusting others
or something?
188:
Or could it be... Yes, it's clear to me
now... You are
203:
Ohhh, and I had him just where I
wanted him, too!
207: Did I, uh... do something wrong?
211:
No, not necessarily. He looked like a
cornered rat, so I merely thought I'd
be able to get some information out
of him, that's all.
213:
Learning even just one thing about
the abyss would have eased your
worries, correct?
221: So... You did all this to help us?
226:
O-of course not! I simply thought
such information would be
important, particularly for my own
research!
235:
Well, if that's all you needed, wanna
head back?
239:
Yes, let's. We should buy Malviola's
favorite treats along the way.
244:
Now hold it right there! Don't just
jump to your own conclusions!
250:
Should you ever wish to collaborate,
I will be all ears.
